El New York Times tiene una bitácora
Estaba yo haciendo mi recorrido diario por las noticias y acabo de verlo:
<a href="http://www.webpronews.com/news/ebusinessnews/wpn-45-20041118NewYorkTimesLaunchesPoguesPostsTechBlog.html">New York Times Launches "Pogues Posts" Tech Blog</a>. 

Está en <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/indexes/2004/11/18/technology/poguesposts/index.html">Pogue's Posts</a>, según su autor:

<blockquote>
an experiment in daily blogging
</blockquote>

Y luego,

<blockquote>
I plan to use this space to answer reader questions, follow up on the other columns, flag emerging tech news issues, point out hilarious or important developments on the Web, share cool tips and write about other topics that don't justify a longer-form treatment. 
</blockquote>

